               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230219-98-person920">
                  JAMES 
                  RAGRAM
               <interp inst="t18230219-98-person920" type="surname" value="RAGRAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230219-98-person920" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230219-98-person920" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I work for Mr. Cooper, who was building a house in <placeName id="t18230219-98-crimeloc569">Peter-lane, Cow-cross</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18230219-98-crimeloc569" type="placeName" value="Peter-lane, Cow-cross"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18230219-98-crimeloc569" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230219-98-off567 t18230219-98-crimeloc569"></join>. On the 25th of January, I left at six o'clock in the evening; the pipe was in the cellar, fixed to the building. I went on the Monday morning, and fifteen feet of it was gone. The house belongs to 
               <persName id="t18230219-98-person921">
                  Andrew 
                  James Smith
               <interp inst="t18230219-98-person921" type="surname" value="James Smith"></interp>
